CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1945, pg. 17, reads: "GAY CELEBRATION - Little Judith West of 2701 Allequippa Street, recently celebrated her tenth birthday. Those present were Ronald Fowler, Helen Madios, Bernadette Coyne, Ronald Moon, Charles Miller, Barbara Jones, Courtney Miller, James Lewis, Earl Lewis, Helen Adair, Francis Carter, Charlotte Carter, Kenneth Smith, James Matthews and Calvert Matthews. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seventeen children, including Ronald Fowler, Helen Madios, Bernadette Coyne, Ronald Moon, Charles Miller, Barbara Jones, Courtney Miller, James Lewis, Earl Lewis, Helen Adair, Francis Carter, Charlotte Carter, Kenneth Smith, James Matthews and Calvert Matthews gathered around Judith West standing behind cake on her tenth birthday, in West home on Allequippa Street
